# Forbidden-pattern list for the pre-commit / commit-msg privacy hooks.
#
# Copy this to  patterns.local  (gitignored) and fill in YOUR machine's real
# values, so they're enforced locally and can never be committed to this public
# repo. One POSIX extended-regex per line; blank lines and "#" comments ignored;
# matching is case-insensitive.
#
# Use SPECIFIC values, not broad regexes, so legitimate placeholders in the repo
# (documentation IPs, example mounts) don't trip the hook. Examples:
#
#   my-hostname
#   203\.0\.113\.[0-9]+        # this host's real LAN/public IP (RFC5737 shown)
#   100\.64\.[0-9]+\.[0-9]+    # tailnet IP range
#   /mnt/myarray               # real mount path (repo uses a generic placeholder)
#   me@example\.com            # your email
#
# Activate the hooks once:  git config core.hooksPath .githooks
